1
00:00:02,280 --> 00:00:04,840
THE BELLES OF ST. CLETES

2
00:00:06,000 --> 00:00:09,629
- Morning, Sammy.
- Norm. What brings you in this time?

3
00:00:09,800 --> 00:00:13,315
- Same thing that always does.
- A little early for a beer.

4
00:00:13,480 --> 00:00:15,835
So float a cornflake in it.

5
00:00:17,880 --> 00:00:20,189
Beer it is.

6
00:00:21,080 --> 00:00:23,719
Seriously,
how come you're here this early?

7
00:00:23,880 --> 00:00:28,635
My supervisor had to go home early.
So he left me in charge of the office.

8
00:00:30,800 --> 00:00:32,950
So l closed it.

9
00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:38,949
Thought l'd stop by, have a few beers
and figure out what to do with the day.

10
00:00:39,120 --> 00:00:43,238
After all, l have 24 golden hours
to spend on Norm Peterson.

11
00:00:44,280 --> 00:00:47,431
- Any suggestions?
- l'd be out there sailing.

12
00:00:47,600 --> 00:00:51,036
Perfect weather,
the waters won't be crowded.

13
00:00:51,200 --> 00:00:54,192
l get seasick, though. l don't know.

14
00:00:54,360 --> 00:00:58,512
Well, you can always go to the driving
range and work on your slice.

15
00:00:58,680 --> 00:01:01,433
No, l don't have my clubs with me.

16
00:01:01,600 --> 00:01:05,479
How about checking out that gym
you've been putting off joining?

17
00:01:05,640 --> 00:01:07,790
l'm not in the mood for sweat.

18
00:01:08,840 --> 00:01:14,949
- Set up that workshop in your garage.
- l'd have to clean it all out first.

19
00:01:15,120 --> 00:01:18,908
You could sit here all day shooting down
my ideas and drinking beer.

20
00:01:19,080 --> 00:01:21,150
Wait a minute.

21
