in the ways of love.

27
00:03:05,400 --> 00:03:09,598
How many women do l have to conquer
to lay to rest this misconception?

28
00:03:09,760 --> 00:03:11,796
One.

29
00:03:12,880 --> 00:03:18,079
All right. l wasn't going do this, but
look what l got in the mail this morning.

30
00:03:18,240 --> 00:03:21,630
- What does that say?
- ''lnflatable Surprises Catalogue.''

31
00:03:23,120 --> 00:03:26,954
My mother sent away for it.
She likes to play tricks on the cat.

32
00:03:28,000 --> 00:03:31,629
This is the one l was looking for.
What's the name on there?

33
00:03:31,800 --> 00:03:35,110
Lanette Cahill.
The Orange Blossom Motel.

34
00:03:35,280 --> 00:03:37,236
Cliffy, who's this?

35
00:03:37,400 --> 00:03:42,997
Some damsel in Florida who l had
a delightful affair with while visiting.

36
00:03:43,160 --> 00:03:46,869
Poor thing. She just keeps begging me
to come back to her.

37
00:03:47,040 --> 00:03:49,508
We're not falling for any of this.

38
00:03:49,680 --> 00:03:53,150
Why don't you believe
that Cliff had an affair in Florida?

39
00:03:53,320 --> 00:03:55,356
- What?
- l believe him.

40
00:03:55,520 --> 00:03:59,513
l mean she could have been drunk,
blind, just out prison...

41
00:04:01,120 --> 00:04:03,475
- Thank you.
- Carla, you got a customer.

42
00:04:03,640 --> 00:04:05,392
Thanks.

43
00:04:12,280 --> 00:04:14,430
Honey, what is it? ls it the baby?

44
00:04:14,600 --> 00:04:18,309
- Baby, hot water, Sam.
- What's going' on?

45
00:04:18,480 --> 00:04:22,871
- What? What happened?
- lt's her. lt's the Evil One.

46
00:04:23,040 --> 00:04:25,713
- Where? What?
- Over there at table five.

47
00:04:28,680 --> 00:04:33,231
- The little old lady?
- Drusilla Dimeglio.

48
00:04:35,280 --> 00:04:39,592
She was the principal
at St. Clete's School for Wayward Girls.

49
00:04:40,360 --> 00:04:45,229
We all hated her guts. She used
to do these mean, spiteful things to us.

50
00:04:45,400 --> 00:04:49,234
l swore vengeance but
she retired before l could do anything.

51
00:04:49,400 --> 00:04:51,470
20 years later, there she is.

52
00:04:51,640 --> 00:04:53,949
lt's been 20 years.
Are you sure it's her?

53
00:04:54,120 --> 00:04:57,237
There's one way to make sure.

54
00:04:57,400 --> 00:05:00,358
She has my teeth mark on her left ankle.

55
00:05:01,880 --> 00:05:04,633
- Go check it out, Sam.
- OK, all right.

56
00:05:06,360 --> 00:05:09,955
- What am l going for?
- l can't do it.

57
00:05:10,120 --> 00:05:14,671
She'll recognise me and then l'll lose her.
Come on, you got do this for me.

58
00:05:14,840 --> 00:05:16,876
Why don't l just ask her name?

59
00:05:17,040 --> 00:05:21,033
That would arouse suspicion.
Crawl over there and look at her ankle.

60
00:05:21,200 --> 00:05:26,115
Much better. No, l am not going
anywhere. Go wait on her yourself.

61
00:05:26,280 --> 00:05:28,236
All right, l will.

62
00:05:28,400 --> 00:05:32,518
You all just watch and see what happens
when she gets a look at me.

63
00:05:46,880 --> 00:05:52,512
- What will you have?
- l'll have gin and grapefruit juice.

64
00:05:59,200 --> 00:06:01,953
She doesn't recognise me.

65
00:06:02,120 --> 00:06:05,954
That means that l can take my time
and work out my plan for revenge.

66
00:06:06,120 --> 00:06:10,033
- She did have a mark on her ankle?
- Mark, schmark. lt must have healed.

67
00:06:10,200 --> 00:06:12,555
l'll think of something slow and hideous.

68
00:06:12,720 --> 00:06:15,029
- l have a suggestion.
- What?

69
00:06:15,200 --> 00:06:17,430
- Do nothing.
- With the body?

70
00:06:17,600 --> 00:06:20,956
No, l'm telling you
to turn the other cheek.

71
00:06:21,120 --> 00:06:24,271
Mooning her isn't enough.
l want to hurt her.

72
00:06:30,200 --> 00:06:32,998
We haven't had any heat for hours.

73
