00:18:39,480 --> 00:18:42,836
- But...
- She didn't have scars on her ankles.

229
00:18:43,000 --> 00:18:46,834
That doesn't mean anything.
Criminals have their ankles altered.

230
00:18:47,000 --> 00:18:49,195
- Jeez...
- So they can wear shorts.

231
00:18:49,360 --> 00:18:55,230
You're ranting. You're sounding
irrational. You're beginning to scare me.

232
00:18:55,400 --> 00:18:59,109
l think you have to take
a serious look at yourself.

233
00:19:01,440 --> 00:19:04,034
Yeah, maybe you're right.

234
00:19:04,200 --> 00:19:06,919
What were you going to do
if it had been her?

235
00:19:11,080 --> 00:19:14,993
l had this storybook fantasy
when l was a little girl

236
00:19:15,160 --> 00:19:19,039
about someday coming up behind her
and shaving her head.

237
00:19:20,960 --> 00:19:24,157
l'm glad it turned out
to be somebody else.

238
00:19:24,320 --> 00:19:27,392
- l guess.
- Look at that, will you?

239
00:19:28,680 --> 00:19:30,910
- l'm late.
- You got a date?

240
00:19:31,080 --> 00:19:34,868
- Yeah.
- Go ahead. l'll clean up.

241
00:19:35,040 --> 00:19:38,510
Thank you, Carla.
l thank you and Debbie thanks you.

242
00:19:39,560 --> 00:19:42,597
You're going out
with Janet tonight, bean brain.

243
00:19:42,760 --> 00:19:45,832
Well then Janet really thanks you.

244
00:19:57,680 --> 00:20:00,114
l wanted her as much as you did.

245
00:20:02,880 --> 00:20:06,236
- Good. Someone's here.
- lt's her.

246
00:20:08,280 --> 00:20:11,272
- Can l help you?
- l think l dropped my wallet here.

247
00:20:11,440 --> 00:20:13,795
Well, let me find it for you.

248
00:20:13,960 --> 00:20:16,394
Let me see. l got it.

249
00:20:16,560 --> 00:20:19,757
- Thank you.
- Not so fast.

250
00:20:19,920 --> 00:20:23,754
l have to be absolutely sure
about this, you know.

251
00:20:23,920 --> 00:20:27,117
- What's your name?
- Drusilla Dimeglio.

252
00:20:33,120 --> 00:20:35,076
Thank you.

253
00:20:35,240 --> 00:20:38,596
Do you believe in fate,
Drusilla Dimeglio?

254
00:20:40,200 --> 00:20:43,237
Well, l never thought about it.

255
00:20:43,400 --> 00:20:47,951
Well, why don't you sit down
and we'll have a little talk about it?

256
00:20:48,120 --> 00:20:52,830
- l think you'll find it interesting.
- l'm kind of in a hurry.

257
00:20:53,000 --> 00:20:55,560
One chair. No waiting.

258
00:21:13,200 --> 00:21:15,430
Who's back there?

259
00:21:15,600 --> 00:21:17,989
Sam, is that you?

260
00:21:18,160 --> 00:21:21,835
l was driving by
and saw the lights still on.

261
00:21:22,000 --> 00:21:24,116
- You won't believe this.
- What?

262
00:21:24,280 --> 00:21:28,751
After you left, l was sitting here all by
myself and guess who should walk in?

263
00:21:28,920 --> 00:21:30,751
Drusie.

264
00:21:30,920 --> 00:21:34,230
- Drusie?
- Yeah, Drusilla Dimeglio.

265
00:21:35,000 --> 00:21:39,471
- Carla, bring me another beer.
- Coming up, Drus.

266
00:21:40,520 --> 00:21:43,990
- She's back there?
- We've been playing pool all night.

267
00:21:44,160 --> 00:21:48,233
- We're tight, Sam.
- So it is her?

268
00:21:48,400 --> 00:21:52,359
Yeah, it's her all right.
But you know something, Sam?

269
00:21:52,520 --> 00:21:57,958
After l told her l hated her, she explained
to me why she was so tough on me.

270
00:21:58,120 --> 00:22:01,908
She was just doing her job.
And maybe l'm a better person for it.

271
00:22:02,080 --> 00:22:07,074
- Anyway, we're pals now.
- l can't believe this. l'm so proud of you.

272
00:22:07,240 --> 00:22:09,231
- This is a turning point.
- Yeah.

273
00:22:09,400 --> 00:22:13,154
Maybe we've seen the last of that
Tasmanian devil of a waitress.

274
00:22:13,320 --> 00:22:17,313
- Bring some more pretzels, too.
- All right, right away.

275
00:22:19,480 --> 00:22:22,472
That's the woman
whose head you were about to shave.

276
00:22:22,640 --> 00:22:28,397
l almost went through with it, too. l came
that close and l could have done it easy.

277
00:22:28,560 --> 00:22:34,430
l mean, she's not as young
as she used to be. But l stopped.

278
00:22:34,600 --> 00:22:37,637
God was testing me, Sam. And l passed.

279
00:22:37,800 --> 00:22:43,397
- Hello there. Come on, it's your turn.
- Yeah, l'll be right with you.

280
00:22:47,800 --> 00:22:51,998
l didn't say l got an ''A'', Sammy.
l just said l passed.

281
00:22:53,040 --> 00:22:55,190
Rack them up.

